\subtree{
\title{Key Concepts}
\p{\strong{PDB ID:} Unique 4-character identifier (e.g., "4HHB") for each structure entry. AlphaFold and ModelArchive entries start with "AF_" or "MA_" prefixes.}

\p{\strong{mmCIF/PDBx:} Modern file format that uses key-value structure, replacing legacy PDB format for large structures.}

\p{\strong{Biological Assembly:} The functional form of a macromolecule, which may contain multiple copies of chains from the asymmetric unit.}

\p{\strong{Resolution:} Measure of detail in crystallographic structures (lower values = higher detail). Typical range: 1.5-3.5 Å for high-quality structures.}

\p{\strong{Entity:} A unique molecular component in a structure (protein chain, DNA, ligand, etc.).}
}

